guide/src/for_developers/README.md
     1‚Üí# For developers
     3‚ÜíWhile `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4‚Üíunderlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5‚Üíflexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6‚Üíconsumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7‚Üíthe book or render it in a different format.
     8‚Üí
     9‚ÜíThe *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10‚Üí`mdbook`.
    11‚Üí
    12‚ÜíThe two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15‚Üí- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí## The build process
    30‚Üí## Using `mdbook` as a library

